18 Article – Tax – Property
19 7–249.
20 (a) This section applies only to nonresidential solar energy generating systems
21 that are approved by the Public Service Commission under § 7–207 or § 7–207.1 of the
22 Public Utilities Article on or after July 1, 2024.
23 (b) Nonresidential solar energy generating systems that are constructed on the
24 rooftops of buildings [or on], parking facility canopies, OR BROWNFIELDS, OR THAT ARE
25 FLOATING SYSTEMS, are not subject to valuation or to property tax.
